==English==
===Etymology===
Yiddish: (large) beans, from the word ''kozebupkes'' meaning goat droppings, from Slavic root ''koz'' meaning goat, and diminutive of Slavic root ''bob'' meaning bean. See Polish wiktionary entry: http://pl.wiktionary.org/wiki/bob
===Noun===
'''bupkis, bupkes, bobkes, bubkes, bopkes'''
#absolutely nothing; nothing of value, [[significant|significance]], or [[substance]]
#:''We searched for hours and found bupkis.''

